    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1933-11-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1933-11-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="588"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d588">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">711.61/343<hi rend="superscript">2/8</hi>
                </note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to the
                        Soviet Commissar for Foreign Affairs (<persName type="to"
                            >Litvinov</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-11-16">November 16,
                            1933</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Litvinov</hi>: I am glad to have received the
                    assurance expressed in your note to me of this date that it will be the fixed
                    policy of the Government of the Union of Soviet Socialist Republics:</p>
                <p>[Here follows repetition of the four numbered paragraphs in Mr. Litvinov’s note
                    printed <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.]</p>
                <p>It will be the fixed policy of the Executive of the United States within the
                    limits of the powers conferred by the Constitution and the laws of the United
                    States to adhere reciprocally to the engagements above expressed.</p>
                <p>I am [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Franklin D. Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
